{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":13761,"name":"","username":"vudugun","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/v/d07c76/{size}.png","created_at":"2016-09-24T20:09:35.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHello,\u003cbr\u003e\nI am trying to mark target points in a tile-based puzzle game. The tiles are beveled cubes exported from Blender with diffuse + normal textures applied.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI have copied some code from the Decals sample (Raycast() and PaintDecal() functions), but when I click on the tiles I am getting inconsistent results:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"http://i64.tinypic.com/34reyl1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe crosshair is a 128x128 image with white circles on black background. I created the material from the material editor:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003e\u0026lt;?xml version=\"1.0\"?\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;material\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;technique name=\"Techniques/DiffAdd.xml\" quality=\"0\" loddistance=\"0\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;texture unit=\"diffuse\" name=\"Textures/crosshair2.png\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;parameter name=\"UOffset\" value=\"1 0 0 0\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;parameter name=\"VOffset\" value=\"0 1 0 0\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;parameter name=\"MatDiffColor\" value=\"1 1 0 0.5\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;parameter name=\"MatEmissiveColor\" value=\"0 0 0\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;parameter name=\"MatEnvMapColor\" value=\"1 1 1\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;parameter name=\"MatSpecColor\" value=\"0 0 0 1\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;parameter name=\"Roughness\" value=\"0.5\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;parameter name=\"Metallic\" value=\"0\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;cull value=\"ccw\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;shadowcull value=\"ccw\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;fill value=\"solid\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;depthbias constant=\"0\" slopescaled=\"0\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;renderorder value=\"128\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/material\u0026gt;\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHandleLeftMouseDown():\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003e    void App::HandleLeftMouseDown(StringHash eventType, VariantMap\u0026amp; eventData)\n    {\n        Vector3 hitPosition;\n        Drawable* hitDrawable;\n\n        if (Raycast(64.0f, hitPosition, hitDrawable))\n        {\n            Node* targetNode{ hitDrawable-\u0026gt;GetNode() };\n            DecalSet* decals{ targetNode-\u0026gt;GetComponent\u0026lt;DecalSet\u0026gt;() };\n            if (decals)\n                return;\n            ResourceCache* cache{ GetSubsystem\u0026lt;ResourceCache\u0026gt;() };\n            decals = targetNode-\u0026gt;CreateComponent\u0026lt;DecalSet\u0026gt;();\n            decals-\u0026gt;SetMaterial(cache-\u0026gt;GetResource\u0026lt;Material\u0026gt;(\"Materials/Crosshair.xml\"));\n            Vector3 position{ targetNode-\u0026gt;GetPosition() };\n            position.y_ = hitPosition.y_;\n            Quaternion rotation{ 90, 0, 0 };\n            decals-\u0026gt;AddDecal(hitDrawable, position, rotation, 0.5f, 1.0f, 1.0f,\n                Vector2::ZERO, Vector2::ONE);\n        }\n    }\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e** EDIT:\u003cbr\u003e\nI just tried changing the size parameter in AddDecal from 0.5f to 1.0f and it kinda works:\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cimg src=\"http://i68.tinypic.com/28jlmpu.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:14:23.654Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":27,"reads":11,"readers_count":10,"score":137.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":2265,"topic_slug":"problem-displaying-decals","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator